      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sorted E46 M3, powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine featuring individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system. This example is equipped with the desirable Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox, delivering power to the rear wheels through a variable M-differential lock. The chassis dynamics are preserved via a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension, with the critical rear subframe reinforcement already completed to ensure structural integrity under high lateral loads. The engine exhibits a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline, and the braking system provides consistent modulation. While the paint displays minor stone chips and the interior shows light bolstering wear consistent with its 'good' status, the drivetrain remains robust and the exhaust note is quintessential S54 rasp. A performance-oriented machine for the discerning enthusiast.",
